Danny Ma — 8 Week SQL Challenge | Case 1: Danny's Diner

Overview

Customer behavior and loyalty program analysis for a Japanese restaurant
using PostgreSQL. Answers 10+ business questions covering purchase patterns,
membership conversion, and menu performance.

Dataset


3 tables: sales, menu, members
Fields: customer_id, order_date, product_id, product_name, price, join_date


Questions Answered


Total amount each customer spent at the restaurant
Number of days each customer visited
First item purchased by each customer
Most purchased item on the menu overall
Most popular item for each customer
First item purchased after becoming a member
Last item purchased before becoming a member
Total items and amount spent before membership
Loyalty points per customer ($1 = 10pts, sushi = 2x multiplier)
Points for customers A & B at end of January (2x points in first week after joining)


Skills Demonstrated


CTEs (Common Table Expressions) — chained multi-step logic
Window Functions: RANK(), FIRST_VALUE()
DISTINCT ON for first-row-per-group queries
CASE WHEN for conditional point calculation
Multi-table JOINs across 3 tables
Date arithmetic for membership period logic
